<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 5:25PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Comanche, Cotton and east central Tillman Counties through 600 PM
CDT...
At 524 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Chattanooga, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Randlett, Faxon, and Cookietown.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 4 and 22.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
